### RAG Eval API — fluxo de testes end-to-end
### Pré-requisitos:
###   1. .env com FUELIX_API_KEY válido.
###   2. docker compose up -d   (Qdrant em :6333)
###   3. uv run uvicorn rag_eval.api.app:app --reload   (API em :8000)
### Uso (VSCode REST Client / JetBrains http client): clique em "Send Request" acima de cada bloco.

@host = http://localhost:8000
@pipelineId = P1
# Setar manualmente após o POST /experiments/run (request 3 ou 4).
@experimentId = exp_REPLACE_ME


### 1. Health check — verifica API + Qdrant + se FUELIX_API_KEY foi carregado
GET {{host}}/health


### 2. Listar pipelines disponíveis (P1..P9, 3 chunkings × 3 embedders)
GET {{host}}/experiments


### 3. Rodar experimento mínimo (smoke): 1 pipeline, 5 queries, sem LLM judges
# Copie o experiment_id da resposta para @experimentId no topo.
POST {{host}}/experiments/run
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "smoke-p1",
  "pipeline_filter": ["P1"],
  "subsample_size": 200,
  "queries_limit": 5,
  "top_k": 10,
  "skip_llm_judges": true,
  "force_reindex": false,
  "force_regen": false
}


### 4. Rodar experimento completo (toda a matriz, com judges) — DEMORADO
POST {{host}}/experiments/run
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "full-matrix",
  "subsample_size": 1000,
  "queries_limit": 50,
  "top_k": 10,
  "skip_llm_judges": false
}


### 5. Status do experimento (poll até status = "completed" ou "failed")
GET {{host}}/experiments/{{experimentId}}


### 6. Report em JSON
GET {{host}}/experiments/{{experimentId}}/report?format=json


### 7. Report em Markdown
GET {{host}}/experiments/{{experimentId}}/report?format=markdown


### 8. Query ad-hoc (pipeline precisa estar indexado por uma run anterior)
POST {{host}}/query
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "What is the difference between a Roth IRA and a Traditional IRA?",
  "pipeline_id": "{{pipelineId}}",
  "top_k": 5,
  "include_contexts": true
}


### 9. Query sem contextos (resposta enxuta)
POST {{host}}/query
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "How does compound interest work?",
  "pipeline_id": "{{pipelineId}}",
  "top_k": 3,
  "include_contexts": false
}


### --- Casos de erro esperados ---

### 10. Query em pipeline não indexado → 409 Conflict
POST {{host}}/query
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "test",
  "pipeline_id": "P9"
}


### 11. Experimento inexistente → 404 Not Found
GET {{host}}/experiments/exp_DOES_NOT_EXIST


### 12. Filtro inválido → 400 Bad Request
POST {{host}}/experiments/run
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "bad-filter",
  "pipeline_filter": ["PX"]
}


### 13. Body inválido (sem "name") → 422 Unprocessable Entity
POST {{host}}/experiments/run
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "queries_limit": 1
}
